.TH "bcm63xx_ep_dma_select" 9 "bcm63xx_ep_dma_select" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm63xx_ep_dma_select \- Helper function to set up the init_sel signal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bcm63xx_ep_dma_select
.BI "(struct bcm63xx_udc *udc "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udc" 12
Reference to the device controller.
.IP "idx" 12
Desired init_sel value.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The "init_sel" signal is used as a selection index for both endpoints
and IUDMA channels.  Since these do not map 1:1, the use of this signal
depends on the context.
